1
00:00:05,237 --> 00:00:12,523
Kīrtan, reproduction, reproducing;
that’s what it is,

2
00:00:12,523 --> 00:00:16,154
so, if we’re reproducing,
what are we reproducing?

3
00:00:16,278 --> 00:00:19,633
[Hi-Fidelity | His Master’s Voice]

4
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:21,637
Someone may say,
“Oh, you mean saying the same thing

5
00:00:21,637 --> 00:00:24,573
over and over again?” No.

6
00:00:24,636 --> 00:00:28,328
That’s why it has to be
an initiated devotee, because

7
00:00:28,328 --> 00:00:35,004
what are you reproducing?
Who is the agent of connection?

8
00:00:35,604 --> 00:00:39,175
So you have to be 
in connection with a real agent

9
00:00:39,175 --> 00:00:44,653
and you’re reproducing faithfully
—like, you know, the word fidelity,

10
00:00:44,653 --> 00:00:47,979
Hi-Fi, now we have Wi-Fi;

11
00:00:47,979 --> 00:00:53,480
before Wi-Fi there was Hi-Fi.
Not high five, Hi-Fi.

12
00:00:53,480 --> 00:01:04,980
It means ‘high fidelity’. Fidelity means
‘faithful’, it is a Latin word: fidelis.

13
00:01:05,104 --> 00:01:12,207
Fidelity means ‘true to the original’,
so they used it in sound:

14
00:01:12,207 --> 00:01:15,633
“This is a high fidelity recording.”

15
00:01:15,633 --> 00:01:28,014
And Gurudev liked the advertisements
for this one company,

16
00:01:28,014 --> 00:01:33,452
“His Master’s Voice”. It was like RCA later,
but they would show

17
00:01:33,452 --> 00:01:39,244
the old-time record player, 
and it has a horn like a funnel,

18
00:01:39,244 --> 00:01:45,419
and what they show is a dog,
and the dog’s like listening to the recording,

19
00:01:45,419 --> 00:01:50,932
you understand? And it says,
“His Master’s Voice.”

20
00:01:50,932 --> 00:01:58,092
It’s saying, it is so perfect that the dog thinks,
“I’m hearing my master’s voice.”

21
00:01:58,107 --> 00:02:02,732
That was the idea behind that picture,
do you understand?

22
00:02:02,732 --> 00:02:06,280
A dog is faithful,
he’s faithful to the master.

23
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,506
“Here’s a recording 
of the master’s voice”,

24
00:02:08,506 --> 00:02:12,743
dog’s sitting there,
“Oh, my master’s voice!”

25
00:02:12,743 --> 00:02:15,736
Gurudev liked that picture very much,
so think about it …

26
00:02:15,736 --> 00:02:19,368
“Vilasatu hṛdi nityaṁ
bhakti-siddhānta-vāṇī.”

27
00:02:19,368 --> 00:02:27,108
Guru Mahārāj is saying, “Let my Master’s voice
play in my heart eternally”—

28
00:02:27,108 --> 00:02:30,506
that’s a devotee, 
that’s a pure devotee.

29
00:02:30,506 --> 00:02:34,090
The Master’s voice
is playing in your heart,

30
00:02:34,090 --> 00:02:38,858
that’s what’s happening to all of us,
every day of our lives:

31
00:02:38,858 --> 00:02:43,205
the Master’s voice
is playing in our hearts

32
00:02:43,205 --> 00:02:50,310
and that’s why we have some conflict,
because we can hear the master’s voice

33
00:02:50,310 --> 00:02:57,458
playing in the heart, and then realise,
“I need to improve.”

34
00:02:58,259 --> 00:03:00,223
But the real devotees
aren’t saying,

35
00:03:00,223 --> 00:03:05,202
“Oh, I don’t want to hear that voice,
I want to do wrong.

36
00:03:05,202 --> 00:03:08,092
I don’t want to hear that voice,
I want to do some wrong.”

37
00:03:08,092 --> 00:03:12,255
No, real devotees say,
“No, may I be so blessed,

38
00:03:12,255 --> 00:03:19,040
fortunate, that I may hear 
my master’s voice in my heart eternally.”

39
00:03:19,194 --> 00:03:31,530
And hi-fidelity: try and be faithful
to what is heard. That’s what it is.

